metadata.description:
Connect side by side object with matching shape or color inside a grid system.

three line for matching shape and color

metadata.name: Jajim #17
metadata.description:
The main idea of the "Jajim" is to divide a square into smaller parts in such a way that each variation has its original and unique composition. The role of lines is such that sometimes they help the dynamics of the composition and sometimes they appear in the form of texture and its contrast with empty spaces leads to the visual richness of the work. I avoided drawing various visual elements in favor of clarity of composition. Also, in order to avoid exaggeration, I used colors sparingly because I think they will have a stronger impact in their occasional presence.

Created using p5.js.

metadata.name: Sashiko #1
metadata.description:
This artwork is inspired by Sashiko - meaning 'little stabs' - which is the traditional Japanese method of repairing fabric with elaborate embroidery designs. This method makes the original fabric thicker, more durable and more beautiful. 
Here the plain coloured textiles take a back seat to the stitching, with simple palettes and layouts.
Keys 2, 3 and 4 will render the artwork at increasing resolutions.

metadata.name: Fizz 2.0 #216
metadata.description:
Experimental Art.

This piece is inspired by a mathematical theorem known as 'Circle packing'. This algorithm aims to cram a bunch of circles into space as tightly as possible. This is a well-explored topic throughout the history of mathematics, but at the end of the day it's mathematics, it's BORING. So to make 'Fizz' a little bit thrilling and different, I wrote an algorithm that randomly draws 450 circles with totally different radiuses (range(width * 0.1, width * 0.001) to be exact) on a canvas, and checks each circle, if the randomly chosen location is a good fit for a new circle to avoid collisions.

Combined with some cool colors and gradients for both the background and the circles, this procedure is all it took to produce 'Fizz'.
Bereft of meaning, feel free to interpret it as you please.
